SIMPLE: coralline
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Coralline
<hw>Cor"al*line</hw> <pr>(? ⟦or⟧ ?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. L.
<ets>corallinus</ets> coralred.]</ety> <def>Composed of corallines;
<as>as, <ex>coralline</ex> limestone</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Coralline</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Coralline
<hw>Cor"al*line</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>coralline</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A
submarine, semicalcareous or calcareous plant, consisting of many
jointed branches.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Formerly any slender coral-like
animal; -- sometimes applied more particularly to bryozoan
corals.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Corallinite</ent>⟦br⟧
